## Updated Stack

| Layer              | Tool                              |
| ------------------ | --------------------------------- |
| Frontend hosting   | **GitHub Pages**                  |
| Frontend framework | **React + Vite**                  |
| Database           | **Supabase Postgres**             |
| Auth               | **Supabase Auth**                 |
| File storage       | **Supabase Storage**              |
| AI                 | **Gemini API**                    |
| Backend/API        | **Supabase Edge Functions**       |
| Deployment         | **GitHub Actions → GitHub Pages** |

## Important Architecture Change

Because **GitHub Pages only hosts static frontend files**, you should not use a traditional backend server there.

Use this instead:

```text
React PWA on GitHub Pages
        |
        v
Supabase
├── Postgres database
├── Auth
├── Storage
├── Row Level Security
└── Edge Functions
        |
        v
Gemini API
```

## Why This Is Better for Your Budget

* GitHub Pages is free for static hosting.
* Supabase gives you database, auth, storage, and serverless functions.
* Gemini handles AI receipt reading, search assistance, and recommendations.
* No separate backend hosting required.

## Revised Recommendation

Use:

```text
React + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind
Supabase Auth
Supabase Postgres
Supabase Storage
Supabase Edge Functions
Gemini API
GitHub Pages
```

Avoid:

```text
Next.js server-side rendering
NestJS backend
Railway/Render backend hosting
```

For GitHub Pages, **Vite React** is simpler and safer than Next.js.

